  <h4>Appearance Tips for Women</h4> 

<div>
    <p id="fixed">Women have an almost overwhelming amount of choices to make when it comes to choosing what to wear to an interview. These choices varies from pant suits to skirted suits or even a dress under a jacket. Moderate height heels for flats are great when accompanied by hoistery in a neutral color; tan, black, and neutral are very safe bets. 
    </p>

    <p>Standard interview attire for women often comes in very conservatice colors, such as black, dark navy, gray, beige, brown, or even red. Skirt lengths should be a little below the knees and not shorter than above the knees. </p>



  <h4>Appearance Tips for Men</h4>

    <p id="fixed">A conservatice black, dark navy, or gray two-piece business suit is a very clean and professional choice for an interview. Long-sleeved button-down dress shirt, a conservative tie, and dress shoes are great starting points. If possible, try to match your belt with your shoes. If you do not own a suit or the company is a bit more on the informal side, go for a conservatice sport coat, nicely pressed slacks, and a white long-sleeved button-down. 
    </p>



  <h3>More Resources</h3>
    <p>If you are having trouble finding affordable business attire, the following organization may be able to offer you some help.</p>

    <h4><a href="https://www.dressforsuccess.org/" target="_blank">Dress for Success</a></h4>
      <p>Dress for Success had been very successful in helping homeless or low-income women by providing them with a free suit for a job interview. In addition, once these women had landed the job, they can return for an additional work outfit. This organization operate on a referral-only basis, which can be obtained through many women's shelters and other social services organization. </p>

    <h4><a href="https://www.projecthomelessconnect.org/get-help/services/" target="_blank">Project Homeless Connect</a></h4>
      <p>Project Homeless Connect provides a number of services for those that needs it. These services range from house searches to free haircuts. This also includes clothings and hygiene supplies. They also have a denture and vision services program. They are located at 25 Van Ness Ave, Suit 340 San Francisco, CA 94102.</p>
